() Tj
T*
(### Backend) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The Flask backend is responsible for:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- validating assessment input,) Tj
T*
(- computing preview and saved assessment results,) Tj
T*
(- persisting records,) Tj
T*
(- serving record lookup and deletion,) Tj
T*
(- generating PDFs,) Tj
T*
(- exposing model statistics,) Tj
T*
(- running quality checks,) Tj
T*
(- serving sample and database metadata,) Tj
T*
(- supporting adaptive screening requests.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Core Logic) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The core Python package handles:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- questionnaire definitions,) Tj
T*
(- feature extraction,) Tj
T*
(- inference and confidence estimation,) Tj
T*
(- storage,) Tj
T*
(- PDF reporting,) Tj
T*
(- training and bundle generation,) Tj
T*
(- model metadata summarization.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## Functional Workflow) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The system works in this order:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. The user selects a language.) Tj
T*
(2. The user enters profile details and consent.) Tj
T*
(3. The user completes the questionnaire.) Tj
T*
(4. The user adds a narrative description.) Tj
T*
(5. Optional audio, image, or passive biomarker inputs are added.) Tj
T*
(6. The dashboard generates a live preview.) Tj
T*
(7. The user saves the assessment.) Tj
T*
(8. The record appears in the records and analytics views.) Tj
T*
(9. The user can later fetch, export, delete, or hide the record.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(If the backend is unavailable, the dashboard can still show a limited preview and queue the record for later sync.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## Proposed Technical Method) Tj
ET
