() Tj
T*
(The system combines multiple evidence sources:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- questionnaire domain scores,) Tj
T*
(- narrative NLP,) Tj
T*
(- speech or audio metadata,) Tj
T*
(- facial/image metadata,) Tj
T*
(- passive biomarker traces,) Tj
T*
(- trained bundle metadata,) Tj
T*
(- fallback heuristics when trained inference is unavailable.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The weaker text/audio/image domains are now handled with targeted calibration and bundle prioritization instead of broad bundle rewrites.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The final output includes:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- per-domain risk labels,) Tj
T*
(- overall confidence,) Tj
T*
(- recommendation text,) Tj
T*
(- screening disclaimer,) Tj
T*
(- modality quality summaries,) Tj
T*
(- trajectory and trend information.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## Multilingual Strategy) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The UI is designed so the active language changes more than labels. It also changes:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- validated instrument display,) Tj
T*
(- recommendations,) Tj
T*
(- disclaimers,) Tj
T*
(- offline messages,) Tj
T*
(- quality-check explanations,) Tj
T*
(- and adaptive-screening prompts.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This matters because a mental health screening tool must be understandable to the actual user, not only technically correct.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## ONNX and Bundle Strategy) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The repository now keeps both:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- the original pickle bundles,) Tj
T*
(- and the exported ONNX artifacts.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This is useful because it preserves compatibility while also making deployment and portability easier for supported estimators.) Tj
T*
() Tj
ET
endstream
