(## Evaluation Plan) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The project should be evaluated with:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- accuracy,) Tj
T*
(- macro F1,) Tj
T*
(- calibration or Brier score,) Tj
T*
(- ROC AUC where appropriate,) Tj
T*
(- offline success rate,) Tj
T*
(- adaptive completion rate,) Tj
T*
(- usability feedback,) Tj
T*
(- multilingual consistency,) Tj
T*
(- record completeness.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The strongest evaluation approach is an ablation study:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- questionnaire only,) Tj
T*
(- questionnaire + text,) Tj
T*
(- questionnaire + text + audio,) Tj
T*
(- questionnaire + text + image,) Tj
T*
(- questionnaire + text + audio + image + passive,) Tj
T*
(- backend mode versus offline fallback mode.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(For the current codebase, a practical follow-up evaluation is:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- compare the upgraded image_dl bundle against classical image,) Tj
T*
(- compare the main audio bundle against the auxiliary audio branches,) Tj
T*
(- compare text_transformer against classical text,) Tj
T*
(- retrain and validate comorbidity only after the upstream bundle priorities stabilize.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## Ethics and Safety) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The system is a screening tool, not a diagnosis engine.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The proposal requires that:) Tj
T*
() Tj
